That's our futon.
That's my futon.

13
00:01:15,308 --> 00:01:17,208
I'm takin' the—
Can I please take the futon?

14
00:01:18,344 --> 00:01:20,209
Please?

15
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:23,100
-Get in the car!
-Violence is not the answer!

16
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,210
Don't be drivin' back here
in a couple days, okay?

17
00:01:25,318 --> 00:01:28,481
I'm not going through this
over and over and over.

18
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:31,284
I'm not…
That's on the tape.

19
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:33,689
I think that's point
number 4 on the tape

20
00:01:33,793 --> 00:01:36,785
because I have my vision,
you have your vision

21
00:01:36,896 --> 00:01:39,160
and I'm leaving, because
the Tantoonis need me.

22
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:41,700
-The who?
-The Tantoonis.

23
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:42,900
What is…?

24
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,200
It's an Indian tribe.
It was in the newspaper.

25
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:46,261
It was on CNN!
You don't even watch TV.

26
00:01:46,372 --> 00:01:48,600
You don't read the paper.
You don't know what's going on in the world!

27
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:50,741
That's one of my reasons.
That's point 1!

28
00:01:50,844 --> 00:01:54,600
-You can't just walk out, Sean.
-Listen, listen.

29
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:58,100
I'm gonna go,
and I'm not coming back.

30
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,685
-Take Fidel.
-Please take Fidel.

31
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,279
I'm not taking Fidel, Sean.
I'm not taking your fucking cat!

32
00:02:04,390 --> 00:02:06,358
I don't have the time and
energy to take care of the cat.

33
00:02:06,459 --> 00:02:08,359
I have to go and get
something accomplished.

34
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:11,953
That cat would be in the way—
Ow! I am a man of peace!

35
00:02:12,065 --> 00:02:14,499
You are a woman of violence.
I'm not a man like that.

36
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:17,570
And you're turning me into that man.
That's like point number 8. I don't know.

37
00:03:22,502 --> 00:03:24,834
-Hi. Good night.
-Good night, Erin. Have a good night.

38
00:03:24,938 --> 00:03:27,338
<i>Dr. Kravitz, you have a visitor</i>
<i>in the main lobby.</i>

39
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:30,034
<i>Dr. Kravitz, a visitor</i>
<i>in the main lobby.</i>

40
00:03:31,544 --> 00:03:35,200
Do you guys know Bob, that
security guard from the lobby?

41
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:37,513
-He's really something, huh?
-Yeah.

42
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:40,560
He asked me to go to this little soiree
with him on Saturday to the aquarium,

43
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,960
'cause that's where
he used to work,

44
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,160
and then yesterday he drops,

45
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:49,289
like he mentions that
Rick hit on him last summer.

46
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:52,000
Oh, he didn't say that!
I only flirted.

47
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:55,067
It was his uniform.
I couldn't resist!

48
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:56,860
I know, but the thing is

49
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:59,260
that he said some really
mean and nasty things about you.

50
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:01,300
They made me feel
really bad.

51
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,534
All right,
so he's a homophobic prick.

52
00:04:03,643 --> 00:04:06,134
So what else is new?
Story of my life.

53
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:08,578
I already said yes,
that I would go.

54
00:04:08,681 --> 00:04:11,100
-You left me the witches' costume?
-Honey, it's you!

55
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:12,400
Thank you very much.
I really appreciate it.

56
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:13,900
You're confused, honey.

57
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,581
What would you do
if you were me, Erin?

58
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,590
Well, you want to get out of it?

59
00:04:19,692 --> 00:04:21,592
Yeah.

60
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,960
Tell Bob
that you're meeting

61
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,932
a friend and her "date"
at the party.

62
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,360
And then, when her date
doesn't show up,

63
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,660
she gets really upset,
she wants to leave,

64
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:35,160
you need to take her home
and then you're out.

65
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,743
That's it. It's really simple.
Men are really easy to trick.

66
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,000
Or treat, you witch.

67
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:42,900
That's perfect! I need a friend, though
and I have no friends so

68
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,060
Erin, will you please go with me
and be my friend?

69
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:46,060
No. I hate parties.

70
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:48,900
You always have a reason.
Please come with me.

71
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,115
Oh, Erin, you have just got to go!

72
00:04:51,224 --> 00:04:54,700
I mean, what man could resist
the wicked witch of the west wing?

73
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,760
Listen, my mother
is in town this weekend.

74
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,800
I don't have any time.
I have to be with her.

75
00:04:58,900 --> 00:04:59,900
Yeah, okay, well.

76
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,760
Wait a minute. My mother
is in town this weekend.

77
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,535
Yeah, I'll go.

78
00:05:04,637 --> 00:05:06,600
Oh, thank you!

79
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,000
Trick or treat!

80
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,280
Mama! Mama!

81
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:25,789
Oh, oh, honey!

82
00:05:25,892 --> 00:05:28,554
Mama!

83
00:05:28,661 --> 00:05:32,392
-I want my daddy!
-Mama!

84
00:05:32,498 --> 00:05:34,932
Daddy!

85
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,300
I found it.

86
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,300
-You haven't got much Wordsworth, have you?
-No.

87
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:45,000
I'll let you have that one half price.

88
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:47,000
Oh, shoot!

89
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,600
-Got it?
-Yep.

90
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,800
There you go.
No, no. Don't close it.

91
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,960
You should never close a book
until you've read something from it.

92
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,700
What?

93
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,412
Just a sentence or a word.
It can be very, very revealing.

94
00:05:57,523 --> 00:06:00,287
Just read something, anything.
Read from the top, then.

95
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,760
"When from our better selves
we have too long Been parted

96
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,460
by the hurrying world,
and droop,

97
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,860
Sick of its business,
of its pleasures tired,

98
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:15,500
How gracious,
how benign is Solitude"

99
00:06:43,703 --> 00:06:47,960
Hi, it's Mom. I fly in
at 9:30 tomorrow morning

100
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,974
so I'll see you at the gate.

101
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:53,375
Hope we can have a little fun tomorrow
night. Kick up our heels or something?

