<i>Aquarium Station next.</i>
<i>Next stop, Aquarium.</i>

110
00:08:10,056 --> 00:08:13,048
<i>Welcome to the Boston Aquarium,</i>

111
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:17,323
<i>home of Myrtle the turtle</i>
<i>and Puff the balloonfish.</i>

112
00:08:23,536 --> 00:08:25,504
<i>What's expanding faster than Puff,</i>
<i>the balloonfish?</i>

113
00:08:25,605 --> 00:08:30,200
<i>We are. The North Addition,</i>
<i>coming in 1999.</i>

114
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:32,000
<i>Watch us grow!</i>

115
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,806
Hey, you guys? Who is this?

116
00:08:34,914 --> 00:08:38,008
That is… Fred Astaire?

117
00:08:38,117 --> 00:08:40,017
No, no, no. This is Burgess Meredith.

118
00:08:40,119 --> 00:08:43,953
Remember? I was telling you this yesterday.
You have to recognize that marking there.

119
00:08:44,056 --> 00:08:45,990
-By his neck.
-I knew it.

120
00:08:46,092 --> 00:08:47,992
Oh, he escaped from the tray
again last night.

121
00:08:48,094 --> 00:08:50,358
Oh, don't worry about it. That's okay.
I mean, they always escape.

122
00:08:50,463 --> 00:08:52,363
-Hey, Ben.
-How you doin'?

123
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:55,700
Yuri needs you for a second down in pumps.
He has another pipe leak.

124
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,601
I can't, Ben.
I'm diving in two minutes.

125
00:08:57,703 --> 00:09:00,700
It's a two-minute job.
For you, anyway.

126
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:05,373
Did you have a chance to go over the
Assistant Aquarist application I put in?

127
00:09:05,478 --> 00:09:08,400
Okay, nothing's been decided.
But you're still on the running.

128
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,378
All right. Thanks, Ben.

129
00:09:10,483 --> 00:09:12,508
<i>The dolphin</i>
<i>show begins in…</i>

130
00:09:12,618 --> 00:09:15,644
Ahh, good!

131
00:09:15,755 --> 00:09:19,088
I'm a volunteer diver,
not volunteer plumber, Yuri.

132
00:09:19,191 --> 00:09:21,591
This is the last time I'm comin'
down and doin' you a favor, all right?

133
00:09:21,694 --> 00:09:25,460
I'm not getting paid for this. I don't want
to be down here helping you. No moreski.

134
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:27,658
I do. I do you favor.

135
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:31,168
Yuri, first of all, what's this?
You have half a gasket in here.

136
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:33,795
Where's the other half
of the gasket?

137
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:36,306
<i>Bye!</i>

138
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:23,878
So, that isn't a problem.
Just fax it to the hotel.

139
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:27,086
I'll sign it, and then
I'll fax it back. All right.

140
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:31,254
Now, darling, you weren't there.

141
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:34,265
-And this gentleman…
-I was here, Mom. Your plane was early.

142
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,160
Well, whatever.
I didn't see you,

143
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,560
and I thought
you weren't gonna make it

144
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:42,360
so this very lovely man offered me a ride
and so I took it and I'm sorry

145
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,874
-but I did leave you a message on the machine.
-Okay, forget about it.

146
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:46,877
It gave me some time to walk around.
I went to the aquarium.

147
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:50,779
Wait a minute. Hold on.
Let me make it up to you.

148
00:10:50,883 --> 00:10:53,078
My latest acquisition.
What do you think?

149
00:10:53,185 --> 00:10:55,300
Blinding teeth.

150
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,683
-Well, he's available.
-What?

151
00:10:57,790 --> 00:11:00,691
-They're not all gay, you know.
-Piper!

152
00:11:00,793 --> 00:11:02,658
Darling!

153
00:11:02,762 --> 00:11:04,889
-Oh, hi!
-Oh, my God!

154
00:11:04,997 --> 00:11:09,300
-It's so good to see you!
-I have never, ever seen you in red.

155
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,029
What has happened?

156
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:12,800
Oh, this isn't red.
This is Hollywood black.

157
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,300
You look great.

158
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:18,400
And this—look at this—
this is my latest find.

159
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,738
He is going to be the
biggest thing ever.

160
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:23,815
-Isn't he big now?
-Oh, yes, you know, he is.

161
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:26,300
-It pays the tuition.
-Tuition?

162
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:29,200
-I'm in med school.
-Really?

163
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:32,600
My daughter went to medical
school. Yes, Harvard.

164
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:36,100
-Harvard.
-Yes. She didn't want to continue.

165
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,728
I didn't finish.

166
00:11:37,830 --> 00:11:39,957
She didn't finish because it
was her choice not to finish.

167
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:42,967
She had the highest grade point
average of any female at Harvard.

168
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:45,264
-No, I didn't.
-Yes, she did.

169
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:47,271
-No. No, I didn't.
-Yes, you did.

170
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:49,273
-Piper.
-I did not!

171
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:54,642
-So, what are you doing now?
-I'm a phlebotomist.

172
00:11:54,747 --> 00:11:57,113
You study insects?

173
00:11:57,216 --> 00:12:00,060
She is not a phlebotomist.
She is a registered nurse,

174
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:03,213
a profession her late father
esteemed very highly.

175
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:06,348
And she's a very good one.

176
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:09,257
-I'll see you later.
-It's inevitable to see you later.

177
00:12:09,361 --> 00:12:11,386
Bye-bye, Rory.
Good luck to you.

178
00:12:11,497 --> 00:12:13,829
He'll need it.

179
00:12:13,933 --> 00:12:16,800
So, how's the old place?

180
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,200
It's quiet.

181
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:20,700
Renovations?

182
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,700
We never finished.

183
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:27,907
Have you really been by
yourself ever since that…

184
00:12:28,013 --> 00:12:31,141
that Marxist left?

185
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,242
-He was an activist, Mother.
-Well, it's the same thing.

186
00:12:34,353 --> 00:12:36,844
I must say I was delighted when I heard
you gave him his walking papers.

187
00:12:36,956 --> 00:12:39,720
Sean left me, Mom.

188
00:12:40,826 --> 00:12:43,886
No. And you let him?

189
00:12:43,996 --> 00:12:45,827
Did I have a choice?

190
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:48,399
Dear, sweetness,

191
00:12:48,501 --> 00:12:50,401
light of my life,

192
00:12:50,503 --> 00:12:53,199
with men, you always have a choice.

193
00:12:53,305 --> 00:12:55,205
Well, you didn't.

194
00:13:03,549 --> 00:13:05,660
I am sorry, Mom.
I don't know why I said that.

195
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:09,620
-It's okay.
-There's no comparison.

196
00:13:09,722 --> 00:13:12,782
You're right.

197
00:13:12,892 --> 00:13:16,350
Loss is loss.
It's the same thing, either way.

198
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:19,056
You know what I think
your father would have wanted?

199
00:13:19,165 --> 00:13:23,397
I think he would want you
to move on,

200
00:13:23,502 --> 00:13:27,300
find yourself a new man
and be happy again.

201
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,400
I am happy.

202
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:31,034
Well, there's no crime
in showing it, is there?

203
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:34,306
Look, Mom. I know that you
don't think that a woman

204
00:13:34,413 --> 00:13:38,440
-can be alone and be content.
-What are you talking about?

205
00:13:38,551 --> 00:13:40,815
This is me you're talking to.
Of course, I do.

206
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,600
Oh, come on.
You are never alone.

207
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:45,255
You're always surrounded
by all these people.

208
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:52,020
Listen, what are we going
to do tonight?

209
00:13:52,131 --> 00:13:55,897
I had an idea. Thought maybe
Dodge and I would come over

210
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,400
to the old apartment
and have some cocktails—

211
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:58,400
Dodge?

212
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:01,000
-Dodge!
-Who is Dodge?

213
00:14:01,073 --> 00:14:03,303
The gentleman I met
at the airport. I told you this!

214
00:14:03,409 --> 00:14:05,934
-You never listen to me!
-His name is Dodge?

215
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:08,445
His name is Dodge and we thought
we'd take you out tonight.

216
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:09,500
I have a date.

217
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,900
Anyway Dodge and I thought
that we would have some drinks—

218
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,781
-What?
-I have a date.

219
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:18,015
You have a date! Goddamn you.

220
00:14:18,123 --> 00:14:21,115
What have I been carrying
on about? Who with?

221
00:14:21,227 --> 00:14:23,752
Who is it with? Come on.

222
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:27,162
A girl from work.

223
00:14:30,236 --> 00:14:33,296
This is Wonderland Station

224
00:14:33,405 --> 00:14:35,805
in the Wonderland commuter parking lot.

225
00:14:36,909 --> 00:14:38,934
A quarter-pound of pecorino, please.

226
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:41,171
The price of cheese.

227
